body:
Since the backup file is only created on the first invocation, it will contain the original file without any modifications. Further invocations will then read the backup file, effectively reverting prior invocations.

This can be reproduced easily by trying to install likwid, which will try to install into /usr/local. Work around this by creating a temporary file to read from.

@alalazo @tgamblin @tkameyama
